{% extends "base.html.j2" %}

{% block content %}
<div class="row mb-5">
  <div class="col">
    <section id="about" class="section-header">
      <h1 class="display-4 text-center pb-1">Dry Rock</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        Ever found yourself clicking through forecast after forecast trying to figure out where
        to go climbing at the weekend? Well then you've come to the right place!
      </p>
    </section>
    <hr class="my-4 mx-4">
    <section id="instructions" class="mb-4">
      <p>
        Dry Rock is designed to be a one stop shop for figuring out where to go climbing.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          Select your region from the list on the top left, and select your preferred units from the dropdown on the
          top right.
        </li>
        <li>
          The overview table for each region has a 7-day rainfall summary for popular climbing destinations.
        </li>
        <li>
          Weather values are given colour codes to indicate how good/bad they are for climbing;
          <span class="bg-success-subtle">good</span>, <span class="bg-warning-subtle">okay</span>, or
          <span class="bg-danger-subtle">bad</span> .
        </li>
        <li>
          Clicking on a row in the tables will allow you to drill into more detail for that place and day.
        </li>
        <li>
          Make sure to bookmark your favourite page! ðŸ˜‰
        </li>
        <li>
          Check out the <a href="
              {% if unit_system == 'METRIC' %}
                {{ nav_links[-1].href_metric }}
              {% elif unit_system == 'IMPERIAL' %}
                {{ nav_links[-1].href_imperial }}
              {% endif %}
            ">news</a> page every once in a while to hear about new features.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>
    <section id="app" class="mb-4">
      <h2>Is there an app?</h2>
      <p>
        There is not an app but if you go to the page relevant to you on your mobile web browser, hit the three dots on
        the top bar and select "save to home screen" a link to the site will appear on your home screen.
      </p>
    </section>
    <section id="info">
      <h2>More Info</h2>
      <p>
        Forecast data is provided by the <a href="https://www.met.no/en"> Norwegian Meteorological Institute</a>. Many
        thanks to them for making their data freely available.
      </p>
      <p>
        This is an open source project, the source code is available on <a
          href="https://github.com/Rory-Sullivan/Dry-Rock">GitHub</a>. You can get in touch with me there or just say
        'hi'
        at the local crag!
      </p>

      <div class="row align-items-center justify-content-around">
        <div class="col-auto text-center">
          <a href="https://github.com/Rory-Sullivan/Dry-Rock"><img src="/static/logos/GitHub-Mark/GitHub-Mark-64px.png"
              alt="GitHub logo"></a>
        </div>
        <div class="col-auto text-center">
          <a href="https://www.met.no/en"><img src="/static/logos/NMI-Logo/Met_RGB_Horisontal_ENG.jpg"
              alt="Norwegian Meteorological Institute logo" height="120px"></a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</div>
{% endblock content %}
